%TUTORIAL ----------------- REEQUAL  CLIST HELP  -----------------------
%OPTION  ===>_ZCMD
+
   The REEQUAL  clist provides for setting or resetting processing optio
   for the EQUAL  macro.
   The EQUAL  macro provides for setting up and executing Edit finds and
   changes.  the FIND/CHANGE options are saved for reuse in later
   edits.
   This macro can be used as an initial MACRO or can be called directly
   by the user.  If used as an initial MACRO a set of options control if
   and when prompting is to be provide.

   The REEQUAL  clist can be called with the following options:
      R/RESET,  H/HELP,  P/PROMPT

   For more information, the following topics are presented in sequence
   or may be requested by number:

    %1+ Options used when calling REEGAGE
    %2+ Control options set from EQUAL  prompt panel
    %3+ Options used when calling EQUAL  directly
    %4+ Options use when EQUAL  is used as an initial macro
)PROC
  &ZSEL = TRANS(&ZCMD  1,P84EQUH4  2,P84EQUH2  3,P84EQUH1  4,P84EQUH3
                       *,'?')
)END
